708/coronavirus-in-oklahoma-stitt-declares-state-of-emergency/ |title=Coronavirus in Oklahoma: Stitt declares state of emergency |last=Forman |first=Carmen |date=2020-03-15 |website=Oklahoman.com |access-date=2020-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317132822/https://oklahoman.com/article/5657708/coronavirus-in-oklahoma-stitt-declares-state-of-emergency |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Puerto Rico: Governor V\u00e1zquez issued an island-wide curfew through March 30 and closed all businesses not involved in food sales, medicine, or banking.<ref name=\"END Toque de Queda\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elnuevodia.com/noticias/locales/nota/wandavazquezdecretatoquedequedaparatodopuertoricoparacontenerelcoronavirus-2552934/|title=Wanda V\u00e1zquez decreta toque de queda para todo Puerto Rico para contener el coronavirus [Wanda V\u00e1zquez declares curfew for all of Puerto Rico to contain coronavirus]|date=2020-03-15|website=El Nuevo Dia|language=es-pr|access-date=2020-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320052615/https://www.elnuevodia.com/noticias/locales/nota/wandavazquezdecretatoquedequedaparatodopuertoricoparacontenerelcoronavirus-2552934/|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*South Carolina: Governor Henry McMaster announced school closures starting on March 16 <ref name=\":8a\">{{cite web |url=https://www.wistv.com/2020/03/15/sc-governor-closes-all-schools-recommends-all-large-gatherings-canceled-number-coronavirus-cases-rises/ |title=S.C. Governor closes all schools, recommends large gatherings cancel as number of coronavirus cases rises |last=Mallory |first=Laurel |website=wistv.com |language=en-US |access-date=2020-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319210936/https://www.wistv.com/2020/03/15/sc-governor-closes-all-schools-recommends-all-large-gatherings-canceled-number-coronavirus-cases-rises/ |archive-date=March 19, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The city of Myrtle Beach declares a state of emergency and closes city facilities that are normally open to the public, including the city library and recreation centers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wbtw.com/health/coronavirus/myrtle-beach-to-close-public-facilities-city-under-state-of-emergency/ |title=Myrtle Beach to close public facilities; city under state of emergency |last=Fortin |first=Matt |publisher=[[WBTW]] |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316125839/https://www.wbtw.com/health/coronavirus/myrtle-beach-to-close-public-facilities-city-under-state-of-emergency/ |archive-date=March 16, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> 9 new cases confirmed in South Carolina, bringing the total to 28.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thestate.com/news/coronavirus/article241208401.html |title=SC reports 9 new coronavirus cases in Anderson, Greenville, Horry, Kershaw counties |last=Feit |first=Noah |date=15 March 2020 |website=The State |url-status=live |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317174152/https://www.thestate.com/news/coronavirus/article241208401.html |archive-date=March 17, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n====March 16====\n[[File:Hand sanitizer and signs at McCarran International Airport.jpg|thumb|Hand sanitizer and signs about COVID-19 at [[Los Angeles International Airport]] on March 16]]\nPresident Trump issued new guidelines urging people to avoid social gatherings of more than ten people and to restrict discretionary travel. He stopped short of ordering a [[quarantine]] or a [[curfew]], but he said restrictions may last until July or August. He acknowledged that the country may be headed for a [[recession]]. Despite the fact that the [[Federal Reserve Bank]] lowered interest rates the day prior, the stock market fell once again.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/16/coronavirus-live-updates-us-death-toll-rises-cases-testing/5053816002/ Coronavirus live updates: Guidelines call for no groups bigger than 10; Trump says restrictions could last into August] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318042652/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/16/coronavirus-live-updates-us-death-toll-rises-cases-testing/5053816002/ |date=March 18, 2020 }} by John Bacon & Jorge L. Ortiz, USA Today, 16 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Colorado: Colorado announced 29 new positive cases of COVID-19, bringing the state total to 160.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cpr.org/2020/03/16/polis-considering-statewide-closure-of-bars-restaurants-gyms-and-theaters/ |title=Polis Orders Statewide Closure of Seating at Bars, Restaurants |last=Markus |first=Ben |website=Colorado Public Radio |access-date=2020-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041907/https://www.cpr.org/2020/03/16/polis-considering-statewide-closure-of-bars-restaurants-gyms-and-theaters/ |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Michael Hancock (Colorado politician)|Mayor Hancock]] of [[Denver]] orders all bars and restaurants close by 8AM, March 17 (excepting food delivery and pickup) and also bans gatherings of more than 50 people in the city.<ref name=\"CO_mar16\">{{Cite news |last=Oravetz |first=Janet |url=https://www.9news.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/denver-coronavirus-update/73-e04fa1e5-bf55-443a-83ed-6fb3e9d02dcc |title=All Denver restaurants and bars ordered to close to indoor dining for 8 weeks |access-date=16 March 2020 |publisher=NBC - 9News}}</ref> [[Jared Polis|Governor Polis]] expanded the closures by ordering a state-wide closure of dine-in services. Polis also ordered the closure of gyms, casinos, and theaters.<ref name=\"CO_mar16_polis\">{{Cite news |last=Wingerter |first=Meg |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/03/16/coronavirus-colorado-bars-restaurants-dmv-closed/ |title=Colorado governor orders bars, restaurants to halt dine-in service statewide in fight against coronavirus |access-date=17 March 2020 |publisher=The Denver Post |agency=The Denver Post |archive-url=https:/