orted, a man in his 50s who had underlying medical conditions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|title=Man at Wayne County hospital is Michigan's first confirmed coronavirus death|website=clickondetroit.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318231056/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The state also announces 30 more confirmed cases, bringing the total number there to 110.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/michigan-officials-state-has-at-least-30-more-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-covid-19-bringing-total-to-110/|title=Michigan officials: State has at least 30 more confirmed cases of coronavirus (COVID-19), bringing total to 110|website=clickondetroit.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318231055/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/michigan-officials-state-has-at-least-30-more-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-covid-19-bringing-total-to-110/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Minnesota: Governor Tim Walz criticized the federal response to the virus. The state had approximately 1700 frozen samples to be tested, but had not yet been, due to the lack of facilities for testing. The state had 77 positive results out of at least 2762 tests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fox10phoenix.com/news/minnesota-has-1700-frozen-samples-waiting-on-coronavirus-testing-but-tests-are-in-short-supply|title=Minnesota has 1,700 frozen samples waiting on coronavirus testing but tests are in short supply|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*Montana: Governor [[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Steve Bullock]] announces 2 additional cases in Gallatin county, bringing the confirmed total to 12 in Montana.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ktvq.com/news/coronavirus/bullock-confirms-two-more-montana-covid-19-cases|title=Bullock confirms two more cases Montana COVID-19 cases|date=2020-03-18|website=ktvq.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319041512/https://www.ktvq.com/news/coronavirus/bullock-confirms-two-more-montana-covid-19-cases|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*North Carolina: The number of cases in the state jumped to 81.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-north-carolina-jumps-to-81-u-s-number-tops-7000/|title=Number of coronavirus cases in North Carolina jumps to 81; U.S. number tops 7,000|date=2020-03-18|website=myfox8.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319015545/https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-north-carolina-jumps-to-81-u-s-number-tops-7000/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 88 confirmed cases across 19 counties. 26 cases involved hospitalization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|title=88 confirmed cases of coronavirus in Ohio; 26 hospitalized|date=March 18, 2020|website=10tv.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318055740/https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Governor Mike DeWine announces 181 Divisions of Motor Vehicle locations will close until further notice. Five will stay open to process commercial driver license applications and renewals. DeWine asks state legislatures to allow a grace period for people whose licenses have expired. Barbershops, salons, and tattoo parlors are closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-from-governor-odh-set-for-for-2-p-m/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Wednesday update: 88 cases of COVID-19 confirmed|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211617/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-from-governor-odh-set-for-for-2-p-m/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Businesses that do stay open are asked to take their employees' temperatures every day before allowing them entry to work and to send sick employees home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/dewine-businesses-should-take-employees-temperatures-every-day/|title=DeWine: Businesses should take temperatures of employees every day|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211624/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/dewine-businesses-should-take-employees-temperatures-every-day/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Mayor Andrew Ginther declares a state of emergency in [[Columbus, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/mayor-ginther-declares-state-of-emergency-in-columbus/|title=Coronavirus in Columbus: Mayor Ginther declares State of Emergency, confirms 2 new cases in city|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211620/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/mayor-ginther-declares-state-of-emergency-in-columbus/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Oregon: Oregon Governor Kat Brown issues executive order extending the closure of K-12 public schools until April 28.<ref name=\"auto2\"/>  \n*Pennsylvania: The state announces its first death in [[Northampton County, Pennsylvania|Northampton County]] following the addition of 37 new cases bringing the total to 133 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mcall.com/coronavirus/mc-nws-coronavirus-death-norco-20200318-ndbg5g56l5g7rmzukwx67yzmgu-story.html|title=First Pennsylvania coronavirus death reported -- from Northampton County|author=Morning Call Staff|website=mcall.com|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211932/https://www.mcall.com/coronavirus/mc-nws-coronavirus-death-norco-20200318-ndbg5g56l5g7rmzukwx67yzmgu-story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pennlive.com/news/2020/03/pa-confirms-37-new-coronavirus-cases-statewide-total-rises-to-133.html|title=Pa. confirms 37 new coronavirus cases as statewide total rises to 133|date=2020-03-18|website=pennlive|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211933/https://www.pennlive.com/news/2020/03/pa-confirms-37-new-coronavirus-cases-statewide-total-rises-to-133.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*South Carolina: The state confirms more cases of the COVID-19, totaling at 60 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wistv.com/2020/03/18/coronavirus-cases-sc-continue-rise-cases-reported-counties/|title=Coronavirus cases in S.C. continue to rise: 60 cases reported in 14 counties|last=Mallory|first=Laurel|website=wistv.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319015547/https://www.wistv.com/2020/03/18/coronavirus-cases-sc-continue-rise-cases-reported-counties/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Utah: U.S. congressman [[Ben McAdams]] tests positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/utah-congressman-ben-mcadams-says-he-tested-positive-for-covid/article_b9b040dc-9d52-5fb0-853d-afa6040f9987.html|title=Utah Congressman Ben McAdams says he tested positive for COVID-19|last=Herald|first=Connor Richards Daily|website=Daily Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319083543/ht