Los Angeles Mayor [[Eric Garcetti]] promised that no one will go to jail for violating the [[stay-at-home order]] that goes into effect at midnight. However, a major purpose of the order is to provide enforcement for businesses which are not complying.<ref>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ L.A. Mayor Promises 'People Aren't Going To Be Marched Into Jail' Under New Safer At Home Order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320200928/https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Dominic Patten, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> Marijuana dispensaries are classified \"essential\".<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html Marijuana dispensaries are deemed 'essential' in LA, allowed to stay open during coronavirus order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321025617/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html |date=March 21, 2020 }} By Allen Kim, CNN, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Illinois: Governor [[J.B. Pritzker]] issued a stay-at-home order. The order will become effective March 21 and will remain in place until April 7 but could go longer.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/coronavirus-illinois-issue-stay-home-order-13-million-residents-california-n1164901?fbclid=IwAR0hnei6UFmSAf_aiG9deV6sjuK8LQqcB9T1s8mpqSQHe7WR3ILy0pluCZU Coronavirus: Illinois issues stay-at-home order for 13 million residents] By Minyvonne Burke, NBC News, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*New York: Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] issued a state-wide order that all non-essential workers must stay at home. He noted that the number of coronavirus cases in the state had gone from zero on March 4 to over 2,900.<ref name=deadline>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ New York Governor Issues Statewide Stay-At-Home Order For All Non-Essential Workers] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320170143/https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Erik Pederson, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> The same day, Coronavirus cases in New York exceed 7000.<ref name=CNN>\"[https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320204137/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/politics/new-york-workforce-stay-home/index.html |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Veronica Stracqualursi, ''CNN'', March 20, 2020</ref>\n*Michigan: The state reports 225 new cases of coronavirus, bringing the total number of cases there to 549.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases continue to rise, state total now 549 |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/20/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-549/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320203728/https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/20/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-continue-to-rise-state-total-now-549/ |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> A fourth death from coronavirus is reported, a man in his 50s from Oakland County who had underlying health conditions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Officials say Oakland County man is 4th person to die from coronavirus in Michigan |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/21/officials-say-oakland-county-man-is-4th-person-to-die-from-coronavirus-in-michigan/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n*North Carolina: The state activates [[North Carolina National Guard]] to assist in logistics and transportation of medical supplies, as the state reports it has 179 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241363186.html|title=As coronavirus keeps spreading across NC, Natio